			<STRING>, GCMG , KCB (December 5, 1875 - November 30, 1933) was the first Canadian commander of the Canadian Expeditionary Force (a corps of four divisions) on the Western Front during World War I.  </STRING>
			<REFERENCE ID="2" PARAGRAPH-POSITION="34" PARAGRAPH-RECENCY="33" SEMCAT="person" SENTENCE-POSITION="34" SENTENCE-RECENCY="33" SYNCAT="np-subj">
